1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:13,033
<i>Thank you for your sacrifice,
Hazel.</i>

2
00:00:13,167 --> 00:00:15,400
<i>I will be forever indebted
to you.</i>

3
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,367
<i>So you can keep
your end of the deal.</i>

4
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:19,000
<i> Just keep your mouth shut.</i>

5
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:21,033
<i>And don't you dare tell anyone
from Coleen's camp.</i>

6
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,133
<i> I have eyes inside this place.</i>

7
00:00:23,267 --> 00:00:25,200
<i>I'm just frustrated
because until now,</i>

8
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:26,833
<i> I still don't get it.</i>

9
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:28,067
<i> Why is it like that?</i>

10
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:31,133
<i>I just want to be sure
that Dad isn't mad at me.</i>

11
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:35,333
<i>And I just want to know if he's
happy that I'm not in jail.</i>

12
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,633
<i> He is happy.</i>

13
00:00:36,767 --> 00:00:39,067
<i>I hope I get to hear him say
that.</i>

14
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,300
<i> Timo.</i>

15
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:42,500
<i> We didn't come here to fight.</i>

16
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:43,500
<i> Timo.</i>

17
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:45,600
<i>Thank you so much for your help.</i>

18
00:00:45,733 --> 00:00:46,633
<i> Sorry.</i>

19
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>Don't come back here again,
okay?</i>

20
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:51,067
<i> Coleen is free now, Manuel.</i>

21
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,700
<i>But you're the one trapped
with Hazel.</i>

22
00:00:53,833 --> 00:00:57,867
<i>I hope that after everything,
you can finally be at peace.</i>

23
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:59,833
<i>Dad got the chance to call you,
Mom.</i>

24
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:01,067
<i> Hello, Love.</i>

25
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:07,833
<i> Hello, Love.</i>

26
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,233
How are you?

27
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:11,733
I miss you so much.

28
00:01:12,767 --> 00:01:14,900
I miss you so much, too, Manuel.

29
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:16,767
Love, Coleen is safe now.

30
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:19,567
Our youngest can finally be
at peace.

31
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:21,900
But the price we had to pay
hurts.

32
00:01:22,033 --> 00:01:24,167
I'll admit, until now,

33
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:25,933
I'm still convincing myself

34
00:01:26,067 --> 00:01:29,367
that yielding for Coleen
was worth it.

35
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:31,600
But the truth is,

36
00:01:32,700 --> 00:01:37,567
it tears my heart apart every
time she asks me

37
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:41,533
why I let you go again.

38
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:46,400
I wish I could talk to Coleen
to explain everything to her.

39
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:49,700
But I know Hazel
will never allow it.

40
00:01:49,833 --> 00:01:51,533
I understand.

41
00:01:51,667 --> 00:01:54,600
Jeffrey and Andrea understand,
too.

42
00:01:56,567 --> 00:01:58,500
But we have to endure this.

43
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:02,467
- That's what we agreed on.
- Yes.

44
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:06,967
Felma, I'm willing to endure
anything for you and the kids.

45
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:10,733
<i>As long as Hazel keeps her word.</i>

46
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:26,467
Manuel?

47
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:29,167
Manuel, are you okay?

48
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:30,800
Why don't you seem to be taking
a bath?

49
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:33,800
Hazel...

50
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:37,367
I'm just taking my time
because the water's cold.

51
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,667
Is that so?

52
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,600
Do you want me to heat
some water for you?

53
00:02:40,733 --> 00:02:42,300
No, you don't have to.

54
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:44,933
I'll just endure it.

55
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:46,533
Are you sure?

56
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,767
<i> Yes. You can go now.</i>

57
00:02:52,867 --> 00:02:54,767
<i> Hello, Felma? I'm sorry.</i>

58
00:02:55,067 --> 00:02:56,567
I really wanted to keep talking
to you.

59
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:59,667
But Hazel's been knocking
on the door.

60
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:02,733
We're in a very difficult
situation.

61
00:03:03,967 --> 00:03:06,233
Even talking has to be done
in secret.

62
00:03:07,933 --> 00:03:09,867
Please be patient, Love.

63
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:11,467
<i> God is merciful.</i>

64
00:03:12,667 --> 00:03:15,733
Good morning, beautiful ladies!

65
00:03:15,867 --> 00:03:17,000
Uncle Noah!

66
00:03:17,133 --> 00:03:19,033
You're already eating.

67
00:03:19,167 --> 00:03:20,433
Hold on, Sir Noah.

68
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:24,233
Why didn't you call me beautiful
when I opened the door for you?

69
00:03:24,367 --> 00:03:26,033
You only greeted me
with good morning.

70
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:31,167
Sir Noah, don't you find me
beautiful?

71
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,400
Didang!

72
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,800
Oh my. Sorry, Didang.

73
00:03:37,933 --> 00:03:39,600
I'll just greet you again.

74
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:43,033
Good morning to the most
beautiful Didang.

75
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:46,267
Almost beautiful is enough.

76
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:48,400
You know, Sir Noah...

77
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:50,767
I'm not asking you to lie.

78
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:53,700
Mama Mary is the most beautiful.

79
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:55,500
I'm just a runner-up.

80
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:58,900
And Ma'am Felma
is the second runner-up.

81
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:01,633
Oh, wow!

82
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:04,233
I'll tell that to Mom.

83
00:04:04,367 --> 00:04:06,167
Please, don't.

84
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:08,700
She might evict me
from her house.

85
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,667
I won't save you.

86
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,467
Wait.

87
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,900
Where's Felma?

88
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:15,567
She asked me to come here early.

89
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:18,933
I have no idea
where we are going.

90
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:20,267
Mom!

91
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:22,267
<i> Uncle Noah's here.</i>

92
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:27,600
Manuel, let's talk again next
time.

93
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,400
Noah's here already.

94
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:34,267
<i> Hello? Hello, Felma? Love?</i>

95
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:35,200
Hello?

96
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:37,900
Dad, sorry.

97
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:40,733
Mom went back inside.

98
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:42,467
Uncle Noah came.

99
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:46,033
Are they going somewhere?

100
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:47,833
I don't know, Dad.

101
00:04:47,967 --> 00:04:50,600
Maybe Uncle Noah dropped
by to bring something.

102
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:54,100
Or maybe they have something
to discuss regarding FMP.

103
00:04:55,333 --> 00:04:57,300
It's okay. What matters is
that I was able to talk to you.

104
00:04:58,500 --> 00:04:59,667
I have to go, son.

105
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:03,067
Hazel's knocking on the door.
I don't want to get caught.

106
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:04,167
Okay?

107
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:07,100
<i>Always remember that I love you
all so much.</i>

108
00:05:07,233 --> 00:05:09,300
We love you so much, too, Dad.

109
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:48,467
When will you go back to Davao?

110
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:51,267
No definite plans yet.

111
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:56,000
I might stay for another couple
of days.

112
00:05:56,133 --> 00:06:01,567
Actually, I allotted time
for Coleen's case.

113
00:06:02,633 --> 00:06:04,233
Good thing it got dismissed.

114
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:07,800
So you're leaving us?

115
00:06:10,067 --> 00:06:11,033
Come on.

116
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:16,233
Just because I'm going home to
Davao doesn't mean I'll be gone.

117
00:06:17,533 --> 00:06:19,833
I'm always here for all of you.

118
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:22,200
I'm just a text or phone call
away.

119
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:24,900
And I'll be here.

120
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,833
Who would've thought?

121
00:06:28,967 --> 00:06:34,333
You joined us on purpose
to help with Coleen's case.

122
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:41,333
While Manuel had to stay away
to help.

123
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:44,833
Noah,

124
00:06:46,133 --> 00:06:48,700
thank you so much
for everything.

125
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:49,900
Felma.

126
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:52,533
I won't get tired
of thanking you.

127
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,433
Because you're always
there during the darkest,

128
00:06:57,567 --> 00:07:01,567
hardest moments of our lives...

129
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:08,667
bringing light and making things
easier.

130
00:07:09,933 --> 00:07:11,433
You're very much welcome.

131
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:37,267
And now we're going
to have a nice dinner.

132
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:40,900
What? Really?
I thought we'd just stay here.

133
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:41,933
Nope.

134
00:07:42,067 --> 00:07:43,067
Okay.

135
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,067
There's this steak
that I want you to try.

136
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,367
- Wait.
- Felma? Felma, what's going on?

137
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:51,333
Feels like my head's about
to split.

138
00:07:51,467 --> 00:07:54,033
- Ouch!
- What's happening? Felma!

139
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:54,900
Felma!

140
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,200
Noah?

141
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,533
What happened?

142
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,233
How are you feeling?

143
00:08:22,533 --> 00:08:23,700
Hi!

144
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:25,300
Hi. Excuse me.

145
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:26,833
Hi, Miss Felma.

146
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:28,900
I'm Doctor Rosario.

147
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:34,733
Your friend said you had
a headache and felt dizzy

148
00:08:34,867 --> 00:08:37,833
before you collapsed
and were brought here.

149
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:43,933
We have already stabilized
your blood pressure and oxygen.

150
00:08:44,067 --> 00:08:45,633
How do you feel now?

151
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,267
I'm okay, Doctor.

152
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,100
Does this happen to you often?

153
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,633
No.

154
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:55,833
Maybe it's just stress.

155
00:08:56,667 --> 00:09:00,500
I'm just going through
something right now.

156
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:03,300
But, you know,
we can run some tests.

157
00:09:03,433 --> 00:09:10,133
Because losing consciousness
due to a headache isn't normal.

158
00:09:10,267 --> 00:09:12,367
Let's not do that, Doctor.

159
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,267
I don't think it's necessary.

160
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,733
I'll just rest at home.

161
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:21,667
It's best to rule out
anything serious.

162
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:26,467
Felma, I think it's
better if you get tested.

163
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,900
Listen.

164
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:31,800
I'll call the kids and tell them
we're in the hospital.

165
00:09:31,933 --> 00:09:34,600
No. No, Noah.

166
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:35,467
Bring me home.

167
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,867
Felma.

168
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,367
Doctor, I'll sign a waiver
if I have to.

169
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:42,800
And don't worry.

170
00:09:42,933 --> 00:09:45,867
I'll come back
if this happens again.

171
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:47,200
Thank you again.

172
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:49,233
- It's better if you get tested.
- No, no, no.

173
00:09:49,367 --> 00:09:52,200
You need to lie down.

174
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:54,367
Please lie down and rest.

175
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,433
Yes, Felma.

176
00:09:57,433 --> 00:09:58,867
Let's get you tested.

177
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:14,400
<i> Let's talk again next time.</i>

178
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,667
<i> Noah's here already.</i>

179
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,367
Hello, Dad?

180
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,233
<i> Hello, Jeff, son.</i>

181
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:45,867
What's your mom doing?

182
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:48,733
Can I talk to her?

183
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:50,133
Mom went out, Dad.

184
00:10:50,933 --> 00:10:53,067
Is Noah with her?

185
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,000
No.

186
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:57,667
Auntie Paz called her earlier.

187
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,067
She asked Mom to go to FMP.

188
00:11:01,667 --> 00:11:02,700
Is that so?

189
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:06,967
Coleen, Andrea, and I
will go out, Dad.

190
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,833
<i> We'll go to Jessica's grave.</i>

191
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:33,400
Hi, Jessica.

192
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:38,300
I really hope you're
resting in peace now.

193
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:40,800
You've got the justice
you deserve.

194
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,900
The case against me
was also dismissed.

195
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:47,733
I hope you can forgive me

196
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:49,500
for everything I did wrong
to you.

197
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:52,333
I love you, my youngest sister.

198
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:56,700
Are you okay, Manuel?

199
00:11:56,833 --> 00:11:57,400
Yes.

200
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:59,067
Okay.

201
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:00,600
Let's go.

202
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:07,100
Wait.

203
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,900
What are they doing here?

204
00:12:13,367 --> 00:12:14,567
I knew it.

205
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:17,233
You're going to meet your
illegitimate children.

206
00:12:17,367 --> 00:12:18,067
And so?

207
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,500
They are my children anyway.

208
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:21,767
Hazel!

209
00:12:21,900 --> 00:12:24,633
Friend! Calm down!

210
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:25,533
Hazel, wait!

211
00:12:30,567 --> 00:12:31,933
Hey!

212
00:12:32,067 --> 00:12:33,367
You have some nerve!

213
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:36,533
Who told you you could
visit my daughter's grave?

214
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:39,233
Hazel!

215
00:12:44,267 --> 00:12:45,100
Dad!

216
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:47,800
What are you doing here?

217
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,167
- Hazel!
- We don't need you here!

218
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:49,933
Leave!

219
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,933
What are you even doing here?

220
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:57,133
Hazel, stop!

221
00:12:57,267 --> 00:12:58,633
Dad!

222
00:12:58,767 --> 00:13:00,267
Coleen.

223
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:01,267
Dad!

224
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:07,833
Andeng.

225
00:13:27,433 --> 00:13:29,300
I'm sorry, I couldn't tell you.

226
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:31,233
Hazel's keeping watch on me.

227
00:13:31,367 --> 00:13:32,800
It's okay, Dad.

228
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,367
What matters is that
we see each other.

229
00:13:56,933 --> 00:13:58,200
Felma, are you sure you're okay?

230
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,867
I was so worried
about you earlier.

231
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:04,500
I'm okay.

232
00:14:07,033 --> 00:14:08,500
You know what?

233
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:11,700
On the way here...

234
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:15,967
I thought it'd be nice for the
kids and me to take a vacation

235
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:17,267
in Davao.

236
00:14:18,633 --> 00:14:20,467
Really?

237
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,367
You should visit me there.

238
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,500
You should all go.

239
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:26,067
My treat.

240
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,100
All expenses paid.

241
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:28,833
That's too much.

242
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,967
Please, Felma. I insist.

243
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,700
I'm sure you'll enjoy it there.

244
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:34,867
How about this?

245
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:38,833
Consider it a much needed
breather

246
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:41,233
after what you've gone through
with Coleen's case.

247
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:45,400
You're right.

248
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:48,467
So the kids and I
can relax a bit

249
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:51,633
before Coleen goes back
to school.

250
00:14:52,567 --> 00:14:54,167
You know what, Felma?

251
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:58,567
I'm already so excited
just thinking about it.

252
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:02,567
I've long wanted to show
you my world in Davao,

253
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:06,133
which is more laidback and fun.

254
00:15:10,733 --> 00:15:11,500
Dad...

255
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:15,900
I only want to know
if you're mad at me.

256
00:15:17,567 --> 00:15:21,267
Dear, don't you ever think
that way.

257
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,067
I will never get mad at you.

258
00:15:24,367 --> 00:15:26,733
What matters is that
you're okay now.

259
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:28,433
And your problem
is already solved.

260
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,700
Dad, I'm still not okay.

261
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:40,767
I'll only be okay
once you come home.

262
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:44,600
So our family can
be whole again.

263
00:15:44,733 --> 00:15:45,933
Oh, come on!

264
00:15:46,067 --> 00:15:47,400
Let go of my husband!

265
00:15:47,533 --> 00:15:48,467
Hazel! That's enough!

266
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:58,133
Manuel, seeing your kids
isn't part of our deal.

267
00:15:58,267 --> 00:15:59,967
Here, of all places?

268
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:02,100
At Jessica's grave?

269
00:16:02,233 --> 00:16:04,267
You all have some nerve,
especially you, Coleen!

270
00:16:09,567 --> 00:16:10,833
Hi, Sir Noah.

271
00:16:10,967 --> 00:16:12,533
How are you?

272
00:16:12,667 --> 00:16:13,967
Hi, Didang.

273
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:16,433
Take care of Felma for now,
okay?

274
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:18,067
I should go.

275
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,167
All right.

276
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:19,800
Thank you.

277
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:21,833
Thank you. Okay, bye.

278
00:16:21,967 --> 00:16:23,200
I'll walk him to the gate.

279
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:37,300
Ma'am Felma, how was your date
with Sir Noah?

280
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:40,467
Date?

281
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,167
You're giving meaning
to everything.

282
00:16:44,633 --> 00:16:45,900
Wait.

283
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:47,533
Why's it so quiet here?

284
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,400
Where are the kids?

285
00:16:50,533 --> 00:16:52,900
Oh, they went to the cemetery.

286
00:16:53,033 --> 00:16:54,300
They visited Jessica,

287
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:56,633
then would go straight
to the mall after.

288
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:02,133
Why didn't they tell me?

289
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:04,467
Why didn't anyone tell me?

290
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:05,167
Oh, my.

291
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,833
What's this? Senior moments?

292
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:09,900
Andrea and Coleen even invited
you to come with them

293
00:17:10,033 --> 00:17:11,567
during breakfast.

294
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:14,167
And you said you had a date...

295
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:19,100
I mean, you said you had other
plans with Sir Noah, remember?

296
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:33,867
Why are you here?

297
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,767
To show off?

298
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,967
Because Coleen's
case got dismissed?

299
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,000
Is that it?

300
00:17:39,133 --> 00:17:41,800
Hazel, can you just stop?

301
00:17:41,933 --> 00:17:45,300
We're here to pay our
respects to our sister.

302
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:47,733
We offered prayers.

303
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,600
I just wanted to
apologize to Jessica.

304
00:17:52,167 --> 00:17:53,667
Apologize?

305
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,900
Your apology won't fix anything!

306
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,367
- Hazel!
- My child is gone!

307
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:58,567
It's your fault!

308
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:00,300
If you hadn't fought with her,
she wouldn't have hit!

309
00:18:00,433 --> 00:18:02,567
Hazel, can you not blame Coleen?

310
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:04,633
She did nothing wrong!

311
00:18:04,767 --> 00:18:08,100
And for heaven's sake,
can you let us talk?

312
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:12,267
What?

313
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,733
Will you give us
a chance to speak?

314
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:18,733
Or I won't go home with you?

315
00:18:30,967 --> 00:18:32,900
Manuel acts like
he's someone important.

316
00:18:33,033 --> 00:18:36,467
Now that our deal is done,
and Coleen's been cleared,

317
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:39,433
he suddenly has the
nerve to threaten me.

318
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:40,533
I've done everything I could,

319
00:18:40,667 --> 00:18:42,800
but he's just so hard
to deal with.

320
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:48,033
Why did you even stop him from
talking to his kids earlier?

321
00:18:48,167 --> 00:18:48,900
Hello?

322
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:49,800
Nothing's going to change
the fact

323
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:52,000
that they're his own flesh
and blood.

324
00:18:52,133 --> 00:18:54,967
Felma may not have any
legal right,

325
00:18:55,133 --> 00:18:57,700
but her kids do.

326
00:18:57,833 --> 00:19:00,767
And, honestly,
their case is strong.

327
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,300
No.

328
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,167
I won't allow it.

329
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:06,533
I don't want to share
Manuel with anyone.

330
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:10,233
Especially now that
Jessica's gone.

331
00:19:10,367 --> 00:19:12,500
He's all I have left.

332
00:19:12,633 --> 00:19:16,100
So, you want him
all to yourself?

333
00:19:16,233 --> 00:19:17,667
Then take him away.

334
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,600
Go back to Canada.

335
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:22,400
That was part of your
plan anyway, right?

336
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:24,767
We really are going
back to Canada.

337
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:28,133
I just want to finish
our mourning period for Jessica.

338
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:31,000
But after that, Manuel and I
will go back.

339
00:19:31,133 --> 00:19:31,800
Then go.

340
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:33,367
Fight for it.

341
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:35,900
I doubt they'll follow you
all the way to Canada.

342
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,433
They can try.

343
00:19:39,567 --> 00:19:41,533
If they do, I'll lead them
astray like stray kittens.

344
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:51,367
Dad, I'm sorry.

345
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,533
Everything turned into a mess.

346
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:56,933
If we had known Hazel
was with you,

347
00:19:57,067 --> 00:20:00,100
we would've come another day.

348
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:04,933
Kids, I'm sorry for the
situation we're in right now.

349
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,600
I never meant to hurt you.

350
00:20:08,733 --> 00:20:14,567
And I'm sorry I didn't say
goodbye before I left.

351
00:20:16,267 --> 00:20:17,433
It was just too painful.

352
00:20:17,567 --> 00:20:20,367
I don't think any of us
could've handled it.

353
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:25,467
Dad, you didn't
have to say goodbye.

354
00:20:27,433 --> 00:20:28,700
Dad, please...

355
00:20:30,233 --> 00:20:32,500
come home to us.

356
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:38,033
Kids, just because we're
apart again,

357
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:40,367
doesn't mean my love for you
has lessened,

358
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,333
or that our bond is broken.

359
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:46,733
Think of it this way.

360
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:48,667
I'm married to Hazel.

361
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,900
And now that Jessica's gone,

362
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:54,700
I'm the only family
she has left.

363
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:58,167
But you know you're
the ones I love.

364
00:20:58,300 --> 00:20:59,800
You and your mom.

365
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:02,500
Right? You're the ones
in my heart.

366
00:21:02,633 --> 00:21:07,900
Dad, don't let Hazel
blackmail you.

367
00:21:08,033 --> 00:21:10,767
If she's threatening
to kill herself,

368
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,400
she won't do it.

369
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:14,567
She loves herself too much.

370
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,167
She's scared because she knows
she'll end up in hell

371
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:22,367
with all the sins she's
committed.

372
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,300
And Dad...

373
00:21:25,567 --> 00:21:30,600
Wasn't it your plan
to leave Hazel?

374
00:21:30,733 --> 00:21:35,300
To have the marriage annulled,
and then go back to Mom?

375
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:38,133
So we could be a family again?

376
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:41,767
What happened to that plan, Dad?

377
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:48,600
I'm sorry, dear.
I can't keep that promise yet.

378
00:21:50,367 --> 00:21:53,200
There are things I still need
to fix.

379
00:21:54,267 --> 00:21:57,133
But I'm always hoping
and praying that someday,

380
00:21:57,267 --> 00:21:59,167
our family will be whole again.

381
00:22:02,133 --> 00:22:03,967
I miss you so much, kids.

382
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,100
I love you with all my heart.

383
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:29,133
Sweetheart,

384
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:32,300
I hope you're happy,

385
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:36,267
now that Coleen's case
has been dismissed.

386
00:22:42,033 --> 00:22:46,933
I know that even though
she hurt you before,

387
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:51,700
you still wanted her to be free.

388
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:55,967
That's how good your heart is.

389
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:06,500
And about your wish
that we always dream of...

390
00:23:07,667 --> 00:23:08,433
Sweetie,

391
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,733
your wish has finally come true.

392
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,400
Your dad and I
are back together.

393
00:23:20,067 --> 00:23:22,267
We'll be together forever now.

394
00:23:23,633 --> 00:23:25,200
And yes, sweetie.

395
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:27,333
I won't be alone anymore.

396
00:23:29,933 --> 00:23:32,733
Your dad and I
are together again.

397
00:23:32,867 --> 00:23:34,667
We'll never be separated.

398
00:23:35,733 --> 00:23:37,467
That's our promise to you.

399
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:47,133
I hope we can visit Jessica
sometime.

400
00:23:47,267 --> 00:23:48,833
When are you free?

401
00:23:51,367 --> 00:23:52,367
Jessica!

402
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:55,167
- Manuel, wake up!
- Jessica!

403
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:58,133
She's apologizing for herself.
And for you.

404
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:00,700
What did you two do to me?

405
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:03,233
What sin did you commit
against me?

406
00:24:03,367 --> 00:24:04,800
Good day.

407
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:06,433
Good day, Miss Precy.

408
00:24:06,567 --> 00:24:07,467
Manuel, who is that?

409
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:10,700
She's the psychic that Jeffrey's
friend knows.

410
00:24:10,833 --> 00:24:13,100
I'm sorry, but you can go now.

411
00:24:13,467 --> 00:24:14,900
You know too much.

412
00:24:15,033 --> 00:24:17,400
Secrets that aren't even yours.
